  "prompt": "How do you know who viewed you video on Instagram?",
  "response": "As of my last update, Instagram does not provide a feature that allows users to see who specifically viewed their videos. You can only see the number of views on your video posts; however, this count does not include a list of individual viewers.\n\nFor Instagram Stories, you do have the ability to see who viewed them, but this feature is limited to Stories only and not applicable to regular video posts on your feed or IGTV.\n\nKeep in mind that social media platforms frequently update their features, so it's a good idea to check Instagram's official resources or latest announcements for any changes in functionality.",
